  "body": "It looks the validators data effect the hashing state the most(for those others , like historical_roots, attestations, since they are only modified by appending, it's easy to cache the hash). For the active validators,  the the fields except effective_balance in Validator change at most once in their lifecycle, while effective_balances change per epoch. If we move the effective balances together, we probably can reduce the footprints of tree hashing a lot. ",
